('radon-rocks-20mm','Radon Rocks 20mm','Decorative Rock',77.00,'Warm reddish-brown 20mm decorative rock.','Radon Rocks 20mm bring warm earth tones to gardens, paths, and borders. Excellent for naturalistic designs.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','radon-rock.jpg',170),
('red-mulch','Red Mulch','Mulch',75.00,'Vibrant dyed red mulch — bold curb appeal.','Red Mulch delivers a vibrant, long-lasting red color that makes greenery pop.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','red-mulch.jpg',180),
('road-crushed-20mm','Road Crushed 20mm','Sand & Gravel',57.00,'Compacted road crush — driveway and base material.','Road Crushed 20mm compacts firmly and is the standard choice for driveways, parking pads, and sub-base.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','road-crush.jpg',190),
('rundle-50-90mm','Rundle 50-90mm','Decorative Rock',232.00,'Large Rundle river rock — warm rustic centerpiece stone.','Rundle 50-90mm features warm, multi-tone river-smoothed stones perfect for water features and bold borders.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','rundle-rock.jpg',200),
('rundle-rock-20mm','Rundle Rock 20mm','Decorative Rock',217.00,'20mm Rundle river rock — soft tones, smooth finish.','Rundle Rock 20mm is a beautiful, warm-toned river rock ideal for borders, pathways, and decorative beds.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','rundle-rock.jpg',210),
('rundle-rock-40mm','Rundle Rock 40mm','Decorative Rock',228.00,'40mm Rundle river rock — bold warm-tone accent stone.','Rundle Rock 40mm features larger river-tumbled stones in warm earth tones.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','rundle-rock.jpg',220),
('topsoil','Topsoil','Soil',28.00,'Screened topsoil — great for lawns, leveling and fill.','Quality screened topsoil ideal for lawn establishment, leveling low spots, and filling raised beds.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','topsoil.jpg',230),
('wash-rocks-20mm','Wash Rocks 20mm','Sand & Gravel',89.00,'20mm washed round river rocks.','Wash Rocks 20mm are clean, washed, multi-tone round river rocks great for drainage and decoration.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','wash-rock.jpg',240),
('wash-rocks-40-50mm','Wash Rocks 40-50mm','Sand & Gravel',102.00,'40-50mm washed river rocks.','Larger Wash Rocks for bolder decorative applications and drainage.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','wash-rock.jpg',250),
('wash-rocks-40mm','Wash Rocks 40mm','Sand & Gravel',95.00,'40mm washed round river rocks.','Mid-sized washed river rocks ideal for borders and dry creek beds.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','wash-rock.jpg',260),
('wash-rocks-50-100mm','Wash Rocks 50-100mm','Sand & Gravel',110.00,'Large 50-100mm washed river rocks.','Premium large washed river rocks for water features and statement landscaping.','Available for delivery and pickup. Sold by the cubic yard.','wash-rock.jpg',270);
INSERT INTO public.blog_posts (slug, title, excerpt, content, cover_image) VALUES
('how-to-calculate-mulch','How to Calculate How Much Mulch You Need','A simple guide to measuring your beds and ordering the right amount of mulch — no waste, no shortfall.','To calculate the volume of mulch you need, measure the length and width of your bed in feet, multiply them, then multiply by the depth in feet (3 inches = 0.25 ft). Divide the result by 27 to get cubic yards. Our online volume calculator on every product page does this for you automatically.','black-mulch.jpg'),
('choosing-the-right-decorative-rock','Choosing the Right Decorative Rock for Your Yard','From bright Crystal White to dramatic Majestic Midnight, learn which decorative rock fits your design.','Decorative rock is a long-lasting alternative to mulch, requiring no annual top-up. Lighter rocks like Crystal White brighten shaded areas; darker rocks like Majestic Midnight add modern contrast. Consider scale: smaller stones (20mm) suit borders, larger stones (40mm+) suit feature areas.','crystal-white-rock.jpg'),
('spring-landscape-prep','Spring Landscape Prep Checklist','Five quick steps to wake your yard up after winter.','1) Rake out winter debris. 2) Top up mulch in beds to 3" depth. 3) Aerate compacted lawn areas. 4) Edge beds for a crisp finish. 5) Refresh decorative rock borders. Need supplies? We deliver across the city.','garden-mix.jpg');
